## Overview
The DIY Toolkit is a collection of 30 practical social innovation tools, including canvases and questions, designed to help development practitioners invent, adopt, or adapt ideas that can deliver better results.

## Purpose
The toolkit is used to facilitate social innovation by providing a set of simple and quick-to-use tools that can be applied in various contexts.

## How it works
To use the DIY Toolkit, users download the toolkit from the website and apply the different canvases as needed. Printed copies of the canvases may be useful for in-person workshop activities.

## Requirements
Basic stationery items such as pens and sticky notes are recommended to effectively use the tool.

## Reflections
The DIY Toolkit is distributed under the CC V4 license, allowing users to adapt and share the tools freely.

## Related methods (if any)
Co-creation, Horizon Scanning, Defuse and catalyze

## Examples
The DIY Toolkit has been designed for development practitioners and is available in multiple languages.
